communications.subject: California Public Records Act Request: Asset Forfeiture Funds (Fontana Police Department)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

- Any accounting records or statistics on seized real estate, vehicles, firearms, funds in bank accounts, and seizures made by the department, as well as seizures made by federal authorities where the department receives a share under the MOUs the department has in place with numerous agencies describing how assets are to be divided.

- Records and data that outlines what was purchased using money from the fund, including dates, descriptions, and total spent. 

- Any annual reports produced civil asset forfeiture program.

- Documents showing the balance of any funds currently in the department Civil Asset Forfeiture fund.

-A list of all items seized through civil asset forfeiture and retained for use by the department

- Sales of non-monetary assets, receipts of sale for vehicles, or the destruction of other non-monetary assets

-Please also include any information relating to contested seizures. This request does not include court documents for individual forfeiture cases.
 
The period for this request is for the last 10 years.

Preferably released in .CSV form when possible

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Joey Scott

title: Number and impact of data center customers (Benton County Public Utility District)

communications.subject: Washington Public Records Act Request: Number and impact of data center customers (Benton County Public Utility District)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

1. Number of Data Center Customers - The total number of customers categorized as "data centers" or equivalent from January 1, 2019, to the present, broken down by year.
2. Electricity Consumption - The total electricity consumption (in kilowatt-hours or megawatt-hours) attributed to data center customers for each year from January 1, 2019, to the present.
3. Growth of Data Center Customers - Year-over-year growth (in terms of number and consumption) of data center customers from January 1, 2019, to the present.
4. Internal Communications - All internal communications, including emails, meeting minutes, memos, and reports, related to policies, plans, or discussions on serving data center customers, dated from January 1, 2019, to the present.
5. Policies and Guidelines - Any official or draft policies, guidelines, or procedures created, revised, or implemented since January 1, 2019, that address the operation, service rates, or requirements for data center customers.

To assist in processing this request, I am specifically interested in documents, communications, or data related to:
- Power usage and billing structures for data center customers.
- Discussions on accommodating the growth of data centers in the service area.
- Environmental and infrastructure impact considerations related to data center customers.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Robin Monks

title: Eltife and Rathgerber text messages with Robert Black

communications.subject: Texas Public Information Act Request: Eltife and Rathgerber text messages with Robert Black
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Texas Public Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Any emails, text messages, or other one-to-one or one-to-many forms of communication between either Kevin Eltife or Julia Rathgerber, on the one hand, and Robert Black, on the other. This request is limited to emails or text messages on or after January 1, 2025. This request is not (and can not be) limited based on subject matter or keyword.

Please note that this request seeks public records wherever they may be found, including on devices or networks owned or operated by private parties. For example, if an employee uses a personal cell phone or social media account to conduct public business, records created, maintained, or held on the phone or account are public records subject to this request.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Adam Steinbaugh

title: Surveillance technology procured by VA law enforcement agencies

communications.subject: Virginia Freedom of Information Act Request: Surveillance technology procured by VA law enforcement agencies
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Virginia Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

The Department of Criminal Justice Services (DCJS) Summary Report on Surveillance Technology Equipment Procured by Virginia Law Enforcement Agencies, 2024, https://www.dcjs.virginia.gov/sites/dcjs.virginia.gov/files/publications/research/summary-report-surveillance-technology-equipment-procured-virginia-law-enforcement-agencies-2024.pdf, notes that 275 law enforcement agencies reported on their acquisition of surveillance tech equipment. The Summary Report contains tables describing their responses.

I would like to learn what tech each of the 275 agencies have acquired.

Please provide any logs, lists, reports and the underlying data sets that describe the names of the individual agencies and each tech item the agency has procured.  

If the logs, lists, reports and the underlying data sets are not extant, please provide copies of the completed reporting forms from each of the 275 agencies.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Tom Nash, a citizen of Virginia, in coordination with Paul Tepper.

communications.subject: RE: Nebraska Public Records Act Request: Academic Dishonesty Study (University of Nebraska)
communications.communication:
Good morning,

The University of Nebraska has received and assessed your below public records request. Upon review, the University declines to provide records responsive to your request. The University has reviewed the request and determined that the records requested are not subject to disclosure under the Nebraska Public Records Act, based upon the exception contained in Neb. Rev. Stat. § 84-712.05(1). The University also declines to provide records pursuant to the Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act (FERPA), 20 USC § 1232g. The University has determined that any nonexempt material is not reasonably segregable from materials not subject to disclosure under Neb. Rev. Stat. § 84-712.05(1) and FERPA. See Neb. Rev. Stat. § 84-712.06.

I am the public official responsible for the decision to deny this request for the reasons stated above. You can challenge that decision as outlined in Neb. Rev. David,

Please find below information responsive to your public records request for the University of Nebraska.

The University of Nebraska’s four campuses – University of Nebraska Omaha, University of Nebraska at Kearney, University of Nebraska-Lincoln, and University of Nebraska Medical Center each track these numbers separately, and University of Nebraska Medical Center (UNMC) tracks numbers differently than the other three campuses, as explained below.

The numbers requested for University of Nebraska Omaha, University of Nebraska at Kearney, and University of Nebraska-Lincoln are as follows:

University of Nebraska Omaha (UNO)
2021-22: 25
2022-23: 3
2023-24: 33
2024-25: 23

University of Nebraska at Kearney (UNK)

2021-2022: 17

2022-2023: 9

2023-2024: 6

2024-2025: 11

University of Nebraska-Lincoln (UNL)


Case Type

AY 2021-2022

AY 2022-2023

AY 2023-2024

AY 2024-2025

Academic Integrity

238

162

203

216



Upon review, the University has not identified a record for UNMC showing aggregate annual data as requested. UNMC does not maintain a report showing annual report totals or totals by college. The Nebraska Public Records Act does not require a public body to produce or generate a public record. See Neb. Rev. Stat. 84-712(3)(f).



Please let me know if you have any questions.



Sincerely,

Molly McCleery

communications.subject: Florida Sunshine Law Request: Public Records Request - Marion County 2
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Florida Sunshine Law, I hereby request the following records:

I am writing to formally request access to video footage from a police intervention, specifically from the body camera worn by the officer(s) and the dashcam of the police vehicles involved. Article:
https://www.villages-news.com/2024/04/15/walmart-shoplifting-suspect-apprehended-in-golf-cart-at-stonecrest-pool/#google_vignette

Exact date of incident: April 14, 2024
Names of parties involved: Natalie Nicole Martin

I intend to use this footage solely for educational purposes to promote a better understanding of law enforcement procedures and the application of the law.

I understand that there may be associated costs for providing this footage, and I am more than willing to cover any fees incurred. Please inform me about the necessary procedures and the costs involved.

communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: Silvio Berlusconi
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Records mentioning, relating to, or generated as a result of investigation or inquiry into former Italian prime minister Silvio Berlusconi (29 September 1936 – 12 June 2023). His death is widely-known and has been widely reported, privacy concerns under FOIA Exemptions 6 and 7 are voided, as are any concerns under the Privacy Act. For example, see the following BBC article: https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-65877241

Please conduct a search of the Central Records System, including but not limited to the Electronic Surveillance (ELSUR) Indices, the Microphone Surveillance (MISUR) Indices, the Physical Surveillance (FISUR) Indices, and the Technical Surveillance (TESUR) Indices, for both main-file records and cross-reference records of both HQ and all field offices for all relevant names, agencies, organizations, companies and events including but not limited to those cited in the previous paragraphs and/or links as well as a cross-reference with the Southern Poverty Law Center to include any information provided by the SPLC. My request includes but is not limited to 137, 157, 176, 177, 183, 184, 188, and 214 files.

If any part of these documents are exempt from disclosure, please be sure to review and release all reasonably segregable nonexempt portions of responsive documents, as the FOIA requires

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Matthew Petti

communications.subject: RE: [EXTERNAL EMAIL] -  RE: Freedom of Information Act Request #1596158-000
communications.communication:
Thank you for contacting foipaquestions@fbi.gov.  Please check the status of your FOIPA Request at http://vault.fbi.gov by clicking on “Check Status of Your FOI/PA Request” on the right side of the page, and follow the instructions below.

Check the Status of Your FOIPA Request
If your FOIPA Number is [1234567-0] please enter [1234567-000] into the system. If your FOIPA Number is [1234567-1] please enter [1234567-001] into the system. If you have any questions about the status of your FOIPA request, please e-mail foipaquestions@fbi.gov.

FIND STATUS OF FOIPA- Request statuses are updated weekly

Please enter the whole FOIPA number-Example: [1234567-000]

FOIPA:
Results will show the Request Number, Case Type and Process Description shown below:
FOIPA:
1234567-000

Case Type:
FOIPA

Process Description (Will display the current progress of the request)
The FBI’s FOIPA Program is searching the FBI’s indices for potentially responsive documents.
You may be contacted via formal letter for all fees and/or negotiation issues that may apply.

NOTE: Recent requests are entered into the FOIPA database in the order that they are received. Before you can check the status, you must have received correspondence assigning a FOIPA request number and the information transferred to the online database. Status information is updated weekly. If a request has been closed within the last six months the online database will display the following: The FOIPA number entered has been closed, and appropriate correspondence has been sent to the address on file.

Estimated Dates of Completion
Requests are processed in the order in which they are received through our multi-track processing system.  Requests are divided into two primary tracks--simple (under 50 pages of potentially responsive documents) and complex (over 50 pages of potentially responsive documents).  Complex requests are further divided into medium, large, and extra-large sub-tracks based upon request size.  Simple track requests typically require the least amount of time to process.  Currently, simple track cases average approximately 122 days from the date of receipt for processing.  Our complex requests in the medium processing track are currently averaging 1,230 days, large processing track are currently averaging approximately 2,010 days, and extra-large processing track are currently averaging 2,370 days for processing.

Respectfully,

Public Information Officer
FBI - Information Management Division
200 Constitution Drive
Winchester, VA  22602
O: (540) 868-4593
E: foipaquestions@fbi.gov<mailto:foipaquestions@fbi.gov>

Do you have further questions about the FOI/PA process? Visit us at http://www.fbi.gov/foia

Please check the status of your request online at https://vault.fbi.gov/fdps-1/@@search-fdps    Status updates are performed on a weekly basis.

Note:  This is a non-emergency email address.  If this is an emergency, please call 911 directly.  If you need to report a tip for immediate action, please contact FBI Tips at http://tips.fbi.gov/ or reach out to your local field office.

communications.subject: Washington Public Records Act Request: Flock Safety search audits, network sharing, and general order (Orting Police Department)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Records related to the department’s Flock Safety system:
1. Organization Audit in Flock. 
The report should include data logged from the period of December 1, 2024, to the date this request is processed. Per Flock's documentation, the Organization Audit is available within the Insights tab and is defined as searches done within the agency.

2. Network Audit in Flock.
The report should include data logged from the period of December 1, 2024, to the date this request is processed. Per Flock's documentation, the Network Audit is available within the Insights tab and is defined as searches of the organization’s Flock network by any agency in the Flock System.

3. A list of network share settings that include:
3a. Flock networks shared with me
3b. Networks that I’m sharing

Please provide records in their original electronic, machine readable format. For example, please provide csv or spreadsheet files where applicable. Please do not redirect me to your transparency portal.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Rose Terse

State, 3 Wash. 3d 19, 546 P.3d 415 (2024), we are writing to remind you that, pursuant to RCW 42.56.550(6), the one-year statute of limitations under the Public Records Act, Chapter 42.56 RCW begins to run on the date this closure notice is provided to you. If you have any questions pertaining to this notice or your request, your question may be submitted within ten (10) days of this letter. ************************************************************************ Questions about your request? Reply to this email or sign in to contact staff at City of Orting, WA.

Technical support: See our help page

communications.subject: Mississippi Public Records Act Request: Untitled
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Mississippi Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Dear Records Officer,

Pursuant to the Mississippi Public Records Act (Miss. Code Ann. § 25-61-1 et seq.), I am requesting access to and copies of the following non-privileged digital forensic records generated by the DeSoto County Sheriff’s Department in relation to a Cellebrite digital extraction conducted on or around January 2, 2019 involving a laptop and/or digital storage media seized from David Hunter Moore (DOB: April, 28, 1995 , Case No: CR2019-0392GCD).

To be clear, I am not requesting access to any images or video content of an explicit nature, nor to any alleged child sexual abuse material. This request is limited to the technical, metadata, and extraction-related logs and reports generated by Cellebrite or similar forensic tools. Specifically, I am requesting:

⸻

Requested Items:
    1.    Cellebrite UFED Extraction Reports
    •    Any full or partial .ufdr, .xml, .html, or .pdf reports generated during analysis.
    •    These reports include structured output of file system artifacts, timestamps, user activity, and metadata.
    2.    Cellebrite-generated Artifact and Activity Logs
    •    Including file system logs, user action logs (viewed/opened files), cloud sync reports, and app usage timelines.
    3.    Hash Value Logs and Verification Tables
    •    SHA1/SHA256 hash logs for digital files located on any seized device, including CSV or text file outputs.
    4.    Chain of Custody Logs Related to Cellebrite Imaging
    •    Any logs indicating the date/time of imaging, name of operator, device serial number, and actions taken.
    5.    Device Information Summary Reports
    •    Basic device identification info (make/model/serial), OS version, and extraction summary.
    6.    File Path Trees and Artifact Maps
    •    Reports showing directory structure and file placement (including synced folders such as Dropbox, if present).

⸻

Format & Delivery:

Please provide the above records in electronic format (email or digital media). I am willing to pay reasonable duplication fees in accordance with Mississippi law. If any part of this request is denied, please provide the legal basis for the denial in writing and redact only those portions which are exempt while releasing the remainder.

⸻

Urgency & Public Interest:

This request is made in the public interest and for the purpose of investigating potential forensic irregularities in digital evidence handling and attribution. Given the potential implications for due process rights and forensic accuracy, prompt disclosure is requested.

Please respond within the 7 business days required by statute. If you require clarification, feel free to contact me directly at mikegrey@outlook.com.

Sincerely,

Michael GreY

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 7 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Marlon

communications.subject: Wyoming Public Records Act Request: wyoming board license list
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Wyoming Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

1. Complete Current Licensee Database
A comprehensive list of all currently licensed medical professionals in Wyoming, including:

Physicians (MD)
Doctors of Osteopathic Medicine (DO)
Physician Assistants (PA)
Any other medical professionals under Board jurisdiction

For each licensee, please provide:

License number
Full name
License type/designation
Current license status
Initial license date
License expiration date

2. Disciplinary Action Records
For each current licensee listed above, please indicate:

Whether any disciplinary action has ever been taken by the Board
Type of disciplinary action(s) taken (if any)
Date(s) of disciplinary action(s)
Case/docket numbers for disciplinary proceedings
Current status of any ongoing disciplinary matters

Clarification and Scope

This request seeks only records pertaining to current, active licensees
All requested information constitutes public records under Wyoming law
Disciplinary actions are already publicly disclosed on the Board's website; this request seeks the same information in a comprehensive, searchable format
No protected health information or confidential records are being requested
Personal contact information (addresses, phone numbers) may be redacted if deemed necessary

Format and Delivery
I would prefer to receive these records electronically via email attachment in Excel or CSV format if possible, or on CD-ROM if electronic delivery is not available.
In the event that there are fees associated with this request, please inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling the request.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 7 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Vig Sinclair

title: Texas universities: Past and planned student events (University Of Texas Arlington)

communications.subject: Texas Public Information Act Request: Texas universities: Past and planned student events (University Of Texas Arlington)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Texas Public Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

This is a survey of events planned or proposed by recognized or registered student organizations (or individual students or faculty members). I am seeking copies of calendar entries for events that were held or proposed. I am not seeking a search of records held by students or student organizations. I am only seeking information held by the university administration (for example, in an Event Management System, which may be helpful in providing a list of past events and proposed future events). 

If this request is unclear or if I could clarify it in any way, please don't hesitate to ask.

I request:

1. All calendar entries (or Event Management System database entries) for events held or sponsored by a registered student organization, individual student, or faculty member during the final two weeks of each term during 2023, 2024, and Winter/Spring 2025. If your institution's academic calendar does not identify a final date of a given term, please use the final day of exams for the term as the final day of the term.

2. All calendar entries (or Event Management System database entries) for events held or sponsored by a registered student organization, individual student, or faculty member after 10:00 p.m. and/or before 8:00 a.m., between January 31, 2023 and July 1, 2025.

3. All calendar entries for events which are or were proposed to be held by a registered student organization, individual student, or faculty member, where the event is proposed to be held after 10:00 p.m. and/or before 8:00 a.m. This request is limited to events that are proposed to be held between July 1, 2025 and July 1, 2026. 

4. All calendar entries for events which are or were proposed to be held by a registered student organization, individual student, or faculty member, where the event is proposed to be during the final two weeks of a term in the Fall 2025, Winter 2025-2026, or Spring 2026 semesters/terms. Please us the same means of calculating "final two weeks" as in (1), above.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Adam Steinbaugh

communications.subject: Washington Public Records Act Request: Information Relating to the Selection and Performance of Third Party Parking Vendors (City Of Mukilteo)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

I request copies of all records related to the City of Mukilteo's third-party parking vendors (such as those providing payment, license place readers, ticket printers, signage, parking studies, mobile applications like Passport) from January 1, 2020, to the present date. Specifically, I am requesting:

1.    All documents related to the Request for Proposal (RFP) process for parking management services, including:
a.        Initial RFP drafts and final published documents
b.       Evaluation criteria used to assess vendor proposals
c.        Meeting minutes from selection committee discussions
d.        Scoring sheets or decision matrices used in the vendor selection process
2.    All vendor responses or applications to parking management RFPs, including proposals for:
a.        Parking management software and applications
b.        Parking signage systems and solutions
 c.       Enforcement tools (specifically ticket printers and license plate recognition technology)
3.    All contracts, agreements, amendments, and memoranda of understanding with selected parking vendors
4.    All internal communications, emails, memos, and meeting notes regarding:
a.        The selection process for parking vendors
b.        Implementation of parking management systems
c.        Performance evaluations of parking vendors
d.        Any issues or concerns raised about vendor performance
5.    Financial records related to payments made to parking vendors, including invoices and payment records

Sincerely,

Robin Monks

  07/28/2025 Robin Monks 
MuckRock News, DEPT MR186339 263 Huntington Ave 
Boston MA 02115 RE: Police Records Request of May 13, 2025, Reference # P000679-051325 Dear Robin Monks, The City received a public records request from you on May 13, 2025. Your request mentioned: To Whom It May Concern: 

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records: 

I request copies of all records related to the City of Mukilteo's third-party parking vendors (such as those providing payment, license place readers, ticket printers, signage, parking studies, mobile applications like Passport) from January 1, 2020, to the present date. Specifically, I am requesting: 

1. All documents related to the Request for Proposal (RFP) process for parking management services, including: 
a. Initial RFP drafts and final published documents 
b. Evaluation criteria used to assess vendor proposals 
c. Meeting minutes from selection committee discussions 
d. Scoring sheets or decision matrices used in the vendor selection process 
2. All vendor responses or applications to parking management RFPs, including proposals for: 
a. Parking management software and applications 
b. Parking signage systems and solutions 
c. Enforcement tools (specifically ticket printers and license plate recognition technology) 
3. All contracts, agreements, amendments, and memoranda of understanding with selected parking vendors 
4. All internal communications, emails, memos, and meeting notes regarding: 
a. The selection process for parking vendors 
b. Implementation of parking management systems 
c. Performance evaluations of parking vendors 
d. Any issues or concerns raised about vendor performance 
5. Financial records related to payments made to parking vendors, including invoices and payment records 
6. Any studies, reports, or assessments related to parking management or enforcement conducted by or for the City of Mukilteo since 2020 

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes. 

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not. 

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires. 

Sincerely, 

Robin Monks

title: Texas universities: Past and planned student events (Lamar University)

communications.subject: Texas Public Information Act Request: Texas universities: Past and planned student events (Lamar University)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Texas Public Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

This is a survey of events planned or proposed by recognized or registered student organizations (or individual students or faculty members). I am seeking copies of calendar entries for events that were held or proposed. I am not seeking a search of records held by students or student organizations. I am only seeking information held by the university administration (for example, in an Event Management System, which may be helpful in providing a list of past events and proposed future events). 

If this request is unclear or if I could clarify it in any way, please don't hesitate to ask.

I request:

1. All calendar entries (or Event Management System database entries) for events held or sponsored by a registered student organization, individual student, or faculty member during the final two weeks of each term during 2023, 2024, and Winter/Spring 2025. If your institution's academic calendar does not identify a final date of a given term, please use the final day of exams for the term as the final day of the term.

2. All calendar entries (or Event Management System database entries) for events held or sponsored by a registered student organization, individual student, or faculty member after 10:00 p.m. and/or before 8:00 a.m., between January 31, 2023 and July 1, 2025.

3. All calendar entries for events which are or were proposed to be held by a registered student organization, individual student, or faculty member, where the event is proposed to be held after 10:00 p.m. and/or before 8:00 a.m. This request is limited to events that are proposed to be held between July 1, 2025 and July 1, 2026. 

4. All calendar entries for events which are or were proposed to be held by a registered student organization, individual student, or faculty member, where the event is proposed to be during the final two weeks of a term in the Fall 2025, Winter 2025-2026, or Spring 2026 semesters/terms. Please us the same means of calculating "final two weeks" as in (1), above.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Adam Steinbaugh

title: Request on Political Appointees (Office of National Drug Control Policy)

communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: Request on Political Appointees (Office of National Drug Control Policy)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

This is a request under the Freedom of Information Act. I hereby request the following records:

1. A list of any and all political appointments at the agency appointed from January 20, 2025 until the date of your final response to this request.

2. Copies of resumes for any and all political appointees hired since January 20, 2025 until the date of your final response to this request. These records are likely in the possession of the Designated Agency Ethics Official (DAEO).

Please provide these records as available on a rolling basis.

Documented is an investigative watchdog and reporting group that explores the relationship between special interests and government. This request is likely to contribute significantly to the public’s understanding of the operations of the government. Disclosure of the requested records serves the public interest, and this request is not being made for any commercial purposes. Therefore, I am requesting a waiver of any fees. If you do not grant my fee waiver request, please notify me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request be filled electronically by email attachment or other electronic file transfer if available, or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter.  I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,
Nina

title: Use of force (response to resistance) guidance, policies, and data (St Michaels Police Department FOIA)

communications.subject: Maryland Public Information Act Request: Use of force (response to resistance) guidance, policies, and data (St Michaels Police Department FOIA)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Maryland Public Information Act, I hereby request the following records related to this agency's policies on and reporting of uses of force and responses to resistance:

• Policies. 
Any and all policies guiding appropriate and inappropriate uses of force by any member or representative of this agency. These may also include “Response to Resistance” policies and similar guidance.

Please also provide all policies regarding the use of lethal, less-lethal, and non-lethal weapons (for example: TASERs pepper ball guns, rubber bullets, gases, sprays, water, etc.), including all policies regarding borrowing, accessing, or assuming responsibility for such weapons,  tools, and ammunition. 

Please also provide all policies or guidance related to reporting or tracking discharges from or uses of such weapons, as well as any other applicable policies or directives related to the acquisition, use, and reporting of weapons or tools. 

Please also provide all policies and guidance used to evaluate any use of force or adjudicate administrative and internal investigations into any use of force or weapon discharge.

• Instructions for reporting. Any and all instructions and guidance related to the reporting of uses of force by any member or representative of this agency.

• Forms, coding descriptions, and other guidance.
All forms, codes, guides, and guidance used in the reporting and review of uses of force or weapons, including:
Any list of codes or definitions for terms or tags used in the reporting, collection, or review of uses of force. 
A blank version of each form, log, and other documentation used to report or track uses of force by this agency.  
A blank version of each form, log, and other documentation used to report or track the borrowing or use of lethal, less-lethal, and non-lethal weapons
A blank version of each form, log, and other documentation used to report or track any discharge of force from firearms, tools, or weapons employed by this agency
A copy of any guidance, requirements, laws, and policies issued by the state, including those issued as part of grant or other funding requirements, regarding this agency’s responsibilities for reportings uses of force or weapons
A copy of any guidance, requirements, laws, and policies issued by the federal government, including those issued as part of grant or other funding requirements, regarding this agency’s responsibilities for reportings uses of force or weapons

• Use of Force Data 
For the period from January 1, 2019 through December 31, 2019 and the period from January 1, 2020 through July 31, 2020, data on the each use of force by representatives of this agency, including but not limited to: 
Date, time: The date (month, day, year) and time of the incident
Location: Street address, block, and other relevant location information
Subject(s) information: race, ethnicity, national origin, age, gender, resultant or related injuries sustained or alleged, weapon type (if applicable) in the possession of each involved individual, arrests or charges associated with the incident
Officer information (for each involved officer): employee number or other unique identifier used for the officer, race, resultant or related physical injuries, patrol division, unit
Incident details: incident or other unique identification number for the use of force incident
Type of force details: a description of each type of force used
Body camera or other footage: Inventory of any video record was created of the incident and/or a copy of the captured footage from all present cameras
Disposition of investigation into the incident: The current or final status of each use of force incident, including whether challenges to the use of force were sustained or dismissed or if the incident had no or is currently under investigation
Please provide the information as a csv spreadsheet, if possible, and if not possible, please provide incident reports sufficient to show the requested data. 

• Discharge Report Data 
For the period from January 1, 2019 through December 31, 2019 and the period from January 1, 2020 through July 31, 2020, data on each discharge of a firearm and other weapons by representatives of this agency, including but not limited to: 
Date, time: The date (month, day, year) and time of the incident
Location: Street address, block, and other relevant location information
Incident description and details
Tool or weapon used, including any unique identifier or identification number
Number of discharges
Subject(s) information: race, ethnicity, national origin, age, gender, resultant or related injuries sustained or alleged, weapon type (if applicable) in the possession of each involved individual, arrests or charges associated with the incident
Officer information (for each involved officer): employee number or other unique identifier used for the officer, race, resultant or related physical injuries, patrol division, unit
Type of force details: a description of each type of force used
Disposition or status of any investigation or follow-up review of the incident
Please provide the information as a csv spreadsheet, if possible, and if not possible, please provide incident reports sufficient to show the requested data. 

If any portion of materials responsive to this request should be deemed unavailable or non-disclosable, please specifically identify the portions of the records or the specific information that is unavailable and the reason for the unavailability. 

If any portion of this request is unclear or if this request could be modified to reduce the burden of producing responsive documents or provide them more efficiently or expeditiously, please reply with a request for clarification or a proposed modification.

This request is being made by a reporter as part of a journalistic investigation. It is being submitted as part of a project to better understand uses of police force nationwide, which has been of public interest for many years and which is of particular interest to large new swaths of the public following the widely-seen death of George Floyd and the First Amendment-protected demonstrations and public discussion that have followed. There is no commercial interest in the submission of this request or the release of these records.

In the event that there are fees appropriately assessed in association with this request, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter.

I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Beryl Lipton

title: Obama Library: WHTV Tapes of October 21st 2010 visit to Seattle

communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: Obama Library: WHTV Tapes of October 21st 2010 visit to Seattle
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

White House Communications Agency video footage (WHTV content) filmed during President Obama's visit to Seattle on October 21st of 2010.

This is a request to review all footage from that day, including outtakes and rushes.

The itinerary for that day is described as followed:

Arrival at Boeing Field in Seattle
The President Meets With Seattle Family  (location: private residence)
The President Holds a Discussion on Women and the economy (location: private residence)
The President Delivers Remarks at a rally for Senator Murray (UW campus)
Departure from Seattle to San Francisco 

Of particular interest (to me) is of any video from the remarks by Obama given to the overflow crowd that gathered in the Husky Stadium end zone. I was on the rope line, and shook Obama's hand, at the overflow event that day: https://obamawhitehouse.archives.gov/the-press-office/2010/10/21/remarks-president-overflow-crowd-university-washington

It would be wonderful if these could be uploaded to the Obama Presidential Library YouTube page: https://www.youtube.com/@obamalibrary - As other similar requests have been.

Thank you for the Obama Presidential Library's commitment to transparency, and I look forward to the resolution of this request.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Robert Delaware

communications.subject: Re: Freedom of Information Act Request: Obama Library: WHTV Tapes of October 21st 2010 visit to Seattle
communications.communication:

Thank you for contacting the Barack Obama Presidential Library. Please see 
the attached information concerning your FOIA request.

Please be sure to notify me of any change in email address as any email 
returned undeliverable will result in your case being closed.
 
Sincerely,
 
Sarah Cain
Archivist & FOIA Coordinator
Barack Obama Presidential Library

communications.subject: Illinois Freedom of Information Act. Request: BCHS District Residency Investigation Documents
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Illinois Freedom of Information Act., I hereby request the following records:

All documents including internal and external emails and text messages concerning reports of residency fraud involving the family of Melinda and Jestin Squires and addresses 16178 E. Franklin Rd Ewing, IL and 14425 Rescue Church Rd, Whittingon, IL.

Documents pertaining to total number of complaints of suspected residency fraud made to Benton Consolidated High School, number investigated, and adjudication status for school year 2024-2025.

Documentation of BCHS policy for investigating reports of residency fraud.

Records are of public interest to determine how reports of violation of residency laws are applied and enforced and whether there is equal application of the law with regard to public position, status, and relationship to board members.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Chris Webster

title: Texas universities: Past and planned student events (Stephen F Austin State University)

communications.subject: Texas Public Information Act Request: Texas universities: Past and planned student events (Stephen F Austin State University)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Texas Public Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

This is a survey of events planned or proposed by recognized or registered student organizations (or individual students or faculty members). I am seeking copies of calendar entries for events that were held or proposed. I am not seeking a search of records held by students or student organizations. I am only seeking information held by the university administration (for example, in an Event Management System, which may be helpful in providing a list of past events and proposed future events). 

If this request is unclear or if I could clarify it in any way, please don't hesitate to ask.

I request:

1. All calendar entries (or Event Management System database entries) for events held or sponsored by a registered student organization, individual student, or faculty member during the final two weeks of each term during 2023, 2024, and Winter/Spring 2025. If your institution's academic calendar does not identify a final date of a given term, please use the final day of exams for the term as the final day of the term.

2. All calendar entries (or Event Management System database entries) for events held or sponsored by a registered student organization, individual student, or faculty member after 10:00 p.m. and/or before 8:00 a.m., between January 31, 2023 and July 1, 2025.

3. All calendar entries for events which are or were proposed to be held by a registered student organization, individual student, or faculty member, where the event is proposed to be held after 10:00 p.m. and/or before 8:00 a.m. This request is limited to events that are proposed to be held between July 1, 2025 and July 1, 2026. 

4. All calendar entries for events which are or were proposed to be held by a registered student organization, individual student, or faculty member, where the event is proposed to be during the final two weeks of a term in the Fall 2025, Winter 2025-2026, or Spring 2026 semesters/terms. Please us the same means of calculating "final two weeks" as in (1), above.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Adam Steinbaugh

communications.subject: RE: Texas Public Information Act Request: Texas universities: Past and planned student events (Stephen F Austin State University)
communications.communication:
Good morning,

Stephen F. Austin State University is in receipt of your Public Information Act request on June 30, 2025.  Per university policy 02-108 https://www.sfasu.edu/docs/hops/02-108.pdf no events are permitted during the final two weeks of each term.

Currently the university does not have an Event Management System database or other centralized method for recording the information requested.

Organizations may reserve any space on campus that is available for reservation. It will take approximately two to three weeks for a manual search of each space on campus that is available for student reservations. If you would like to narrow your request the information may be available more quickly, please respond to this email.

The university has elected to waive its usual PIA processing fee in this instance.

Thank you,

   April Smith '02 and '19
   Director of Executive Programs and Events
   Office of the President
   Stephen F. Austin State University
   PO Box 6078, SFA Station
   Nacogdoches, TX 75962-6078
   T 936.468.4048
The views and opinions expressed in this message are my own and do not necessarily reflect the views and opinions of Stephen F. Austin State University, the University of Texas System, or its Board of Regents.

communications.communication:
Subject: Outstanding Records Needed — FOIL #23‑05‑237 (“Live Birth Data by School District – Source Data”)

Dear Records Access Office,

Thank you for your correspondence and file deliveries of  18 March 2024 and 24 October 2024 under FOIL #23‑05‑237.  
After a detailed review, it appears that several items described in my original request are still outstanding:

1. Record‑level datasets / source data used to calculate the 2021 provisional live‑birth counts by school district;
2. Programs / logic (e.g., SAS or SQL scripts, lookup tables, data‑processing documentation) applied to create those provisional counts;
3. Any 2022 provisional school‑district birth table generated since the 2021 counts were compiled; and
4. A § 89(3)(a) completeness certification confirming that all responsive records have been produced.

Kindly advise within five (5) business days whether these materials exist and, if so, when they can be supplied in native electronic format.  
If any portion is being withheld in whole or in part, please cite each specific exemption in Public Officers Law § 87(2) that you believe justifies nondisclosure, together with the factual basis for its application.

I appreciate your continued assistance and look forward to your prompt clarification.

communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: "Ensuring Lawful Governance" EO (Environmental Protection Agency)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

The February 19 executive order  “Ensuring Lawful Governance and Implementing the President’s “Department of Government Efficiency” Deregulatory Initiative” (EO 14219) states: “Within 60 days of the date of this order, agency heads shall provide to the Administrator of the Office of Information and Regulatory Affairs (OIRA) within the Office of Management and Budget a list of all regulations identified by class as listed in subsection (a) of this section.”

https://www.federalregister.gov/documents/2025/02/25/2025-03138/ensuring-lawful-governance-and-implementing-the-presidents-department-of-government-efficiency

I am requesting the memo or reports created in response to this order, including any media and attachments sent from the Environmental Protection Agency to OIRA.

I am a member of the press, and the documents will be used in the course of reporting for Chemical Watch News & Insight (https://www.enhesa.com/product-intelligence/our-solutions/chemical-watch-news-insight/).

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Meg Duff

--- Please respond above this line --- 
RE: PUBLIC RECORDS REQUEST of July 13, 2025, Reference #C003439-071325 Dear Mr. Clark: Greetings. My name is Joseph Anderson and I am a Deputy Public Records Officer for Skamania County. I assist inreviewing and responding to public records requests (PRRs) for alldepartments. 

On July 13, 2025, we received your public records request for "- Any and all lists, spreadsheets or other organized datasets that detail potential or substantiated allegations of misconduct and/or impeached or impeachable testimony, created under Brady v. Maryland and/or Giglio v. United States. 
- Any and all records regarding substantiated allegations of misconduct or violations of internal department policy or criminal law by specific law enforcement officers. 

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes." 
After reviewing our files, we have located records that are responsive to your request. Please log in to the Skamania County Public Records Center at the following link to retrieve the records responsive to your request: County Public Records Request - C003439-071325 Pleasenote the following information from Skamania County Prosecutor AdamKick with respect to the first part of your request, as writtenabove, regarding Brady or Giglio material: "[Skamania County does not] have a 'Brady list,' per se.There is one deputy that works for the Skamania county Sheriff’s Officefor whom we have potential impeachment information and for whom weprovide a memo summarizing the circumstances. We provide this memo whenrequired to defense counsel on cases involving this deputy. Becausethere is only one local deputy for whom we maintain PID information,there is no list. Just the single memo, which we are happy to provide. [ Potential Impeachment Disclosure memo attached here .] TheWashington State Patrol sometimes sends us information from state-widepotential impeachment issues with WSP employees. We do not maintain thisinformation in any organized way because it does not apply to anyofficers that regularly appear in our courts/cases. I just want toconfirm that these records are not made into any list, and to the extentthat these records are related to WSP employees, are likely bettersought from the WSP directly, if you’re interested in the raw data (inaddition to any lists)." I have been advised by the Sheriff's Office that there are no records responsive to the second portion of your request seeking records regarding substantiated allegations of misconduct or violations of internaldepartment policy or criminal law by specific law enforcement officers. SkamaniaCounty has searched for, attempted to identify, locate, and provide anynon-exempt public records that may be responsive to this request. Since this completely fulfills your request, we are now closing this public records request. The one (1) yearstatute of limitations to seek judicial review under the Public RecordsAct (Chapter 42.56 RCW) begins now because Skamania County does notintend to further address this request. Please note that if you do not review and download your records within thirty (30) days, they may be removed from the system, in which case you will have to start the public records process all over again to receive your requested records. 

Please feel free to contact me if you have any further questions or concerns by replying to this email or at my phone number below. 

Sincerely, 

Joseph Anderson 
Deputy Public Records Officer 
Office of the Skamania County Prosecuting Attorney 
240 NW Vancouver Avenue | PO Box 790 
Stevenson, WA 98648 
509-427-3791

RE: Public Records Request of July 01, 2025, Reference # R000657-070125 Dear Aspen Ford, Whatcom County received a request from you on July 01, 2025. Your request mentioned: To Whom It May Concern: 

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records: 

- Any and all lists, spreadsheets or other organized datasets that detail potential or substantiated allegations of misconduct and/or impeached or impeachable testimony, created under Brady v. Maryland and/or Giglio v. United States. 
- Any and all records regarding substantiated allegations of misconduct or violations of internal department policy or criminal law by specific law enforcement officers. 

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes. 

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not. 

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires. 

Sincerely, 

Aspen Ford

communications.subject: RE: Washington Public Records Act Request #R000657-070125
communications.communication:
Hello,

Thank you for sending over you all's Brady List and for navigating the email situation. I really appreciate your time and effort.

I wanted to ask if you all maintain any records in regards to the law enforcement officers that show why they were placed on the list. For example, misconduct violations, internal policy violations, instances of dishonesty, etc. I also included this request in my initial request.

Thank you again for your time. Let me know if you have any questions.

Best,
Aspen Ford

title: Texas universities: Past and planned student events (University of Texas at San Antonio)

communications.subject: Texas Public Information Act Request: Texas universities: Past and planned student events (University of Texas at San Antonio)
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Texas Public Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

This is a survey of events planned or proposed by recognized or registered student organizations (or individual students or faculty members). I am seeking copies of calendar entries for events that were held or proposed. I am not seeking a search of records held by students or student organizations. I am only seeking information held by the university administration (for example, in an Event Management System, which may be helpful in providing a list of past events and proposed future events). 

If this request is unclear or if I could clarify it in any way, please don't hesitate to ask.

I request:

1. All calendar entries (or Event Management System database entries) for events held or sponsored by a registered student organization, individual student, or faculty member during the final two weeks of each term during 2023, 2024, and Winter/Spring 2025. If your institution's academic calendar does not identify a final date of a given term, please use the final day of exams for the term as the final day of the term.

2. All calendar entries (or Event Management System database entries) for events held or sponsored by a registered student organization, individual student, or faculty member after 10:00 p.m. and/or before 8:00 a.m., between January 31, 2023 and July 1, 2025.

3. All calendar entries for events which are or were proposed to be held by a registered student organization, individual student, or faculty member, where the event is proposed to be held after 10:00 p.m. and/or before 8:00 a.m. This request is limited to events that are proposed to be held between July 1, 2025 and July 1, 2026. 

4. All calendar entries for events which are or were proposed to be held by a registered student organization, individual student, or faculty member, where the event is proposed to be during the final two weeks of a term in the Fall 2025, Winter 2025-2026, or Spring 2026 semesters/terms. Please us the same means of calculating "final two weeks" as in (1), above.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Adam Steinbaugh

This is in response to your Texas Public Information Act (TPIA) request to The University of Texas at San Antonio (UTSA), received in our office on 6/30/2025, wherein you requested, "To Whom It May Concern: 

Pursuant to the Texas Public Information Act, I hereby request the following records: 

This is a survey of events planned or proposed by recognized or registered student organizations (or individual students or faculty members). I am seeking copies of calendar entries for events that were held or proposed. I am not seeking a search of records held by students or student organizations. I am only seeking information held by the university administration (for example, in an Event Management System, which may be helpful in providing a list of past events and proposed future events). 

If this request is unclear or if I could clarify it in any way, please don't hesitate to ask. 

I request: 

1. All calendar entries (or Event Management System database entries) for events held or sponsored by a registered student organization, individual student, or faculty member during the final two weeks of each term during 2023, 2024, and Winter/Spring 2025. If your institution's academic calendar does not identify a final date of a given term, please use the final day of exams for the term as the final day of the term. 

2. All calendar entries (or Event Management System database entries) for events held or sponsored by a registered student organization, individual student, or faculty member after 10:00 p.m. and/or before 8:00 a.m., between January 31, 2023 and July 1, 2025. 

3. All calendar entries for events which are or were proposed to be held by a registered student organization, individual student, or faculty member, where the event is proposed to be held after 10:00 p.m. and/or before 8:00 a.m. This request is limited to events that are proposed to be held between July 1, 2025 and July 1, 2026. 

4. All calendar entries for events which are or were proposed to be held by a registered student organization, individual student, or faculty member, where the event is proposed to be during the final two weeks of a term in the Fall 2025, Winter 2025-2026, or Spring 2026 semesters/terms. Please us the same means of calculating "final two weeks" as in (1), above. 

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes. 

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not. 

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days, as the statute requires. 

Sincerely, 

Adam Steinbaugh 
We have reviewed our files and located the attached documents that are responsive to your request.  Although the TPIA allows a governmental body to charge for copying documents, the attached is provided to you at no charge. 
If you have any questions or wish to discuss this further, you may contact me at 210-458-7500 / 210-458-4105 or via email at publicinfo@utsa.edu. 

Sincerely, Kathleen Blanton Open Records Manager 
The University of Texas at San Antonio 
Office of Legal Affairs - Open Records 
www.utsa.edu/openrecords **If you wish to make or amend an open records request to UTSA you may do so online at www.utsa.edu/openrecords.**

communications.subject: California Public Records Act Request: ChatGPT EDU user analytics data
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

1) A user data export from the university's ChatGPT EDU user analytics dashboard covering the time period January 1, 2025 until the date this request is processed. A description of this data and how to export it from the dashboard are available here: https://help.openai.com/en/articles/10875114-user-analytics-for-chatgpt-enterprise-and-edu. 

Specifically, I am requesting the data export report described in that help article under the heading "User export - column definitions". Several of the data columns in the export ("name" and "email") contain personally identifiable information and I acknowledge that these columns must be redacted or removed from the responsive record.

2) A GPT data export from the university's ChatGPT EDU user analytics dashboard covering the time period January 1, 2025 until the date this request is processed. Specifically, I am requesting the data export report described in the help article linked above under the heading "GPT export - column definitions." I acknowledge that this report contains one data column ("gpt_creator_email") that must be redacted or removed from the responsive record.

I ask that the responsive records be provided as .csv files or in a comparable, data-friendly file type.

I also ask that all fees be waived as the records I have requested are readily available and can be instantly exported from the user analytics dashboard. The necessary redactions can also be done quickly and in mass by removing the relevant columns from the dataset.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Todd Feathers

communications.subject: Texas Public Information Act Request: Dolores Leschuck Open Records Request
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Texas Public Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Dear Sir or Madam:

I am submitting this letter in order to request all documents, public information and public records related to Case ID 25000541, described below.  Please be advised that this request is hereby submitted pursuant to The Texas Open Records Act, Texas Government Code Chapter 552, and The Federal Freedom of Information Act.  I would like to request that all such public information and records be produced as soon as possible.  Please be advised that your agency will be paid the requisite fees, in accordance with the Open Records Act, with respect to your compliance with this request for the production of public records and documents.

Our office represents Dolores Leschuck in regard to injuries she sustained in an automobile accident  on April 9, 2025 at approximately 5:48 PM.  The location of the accident was 21100 SE H.K. Dodgen Loop, Temple TX.  The public information and documents which I am requesting at this time (including information that is collected, assembled, or maintained under a law or ordinance or in connection with the transaction of official business by or for a government body, which included the media on which the public information is recorded, paper, film, magnetic, optical, and/or solid state device that can store an electronic signal; tape; computer disk; etc.) are as follows:

•	Any video or photographs taken at the scene of the collision, or in the officer’s cruiser,
 
•	Any bodycam footage captured by responding officers,

•	Any witness statements, handwritten notes, or supplemental accident report information, 

•	An audio copy of the 911 calls from witnesses who called in to report this accident, along with any witness names, addresses, and phone numbers that may be in possession of the communications center, along with any police reports that correspond to this particular incident. 

•	Copies of all sketches, diagrams, witness statements and/or names and phone numbers of witnesses at the scene who did not give statements that may be in the possession of your department.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Vic Feazell

communications.subject: Illinois Freedom of Information Act. Request: N6: Parent Restriction Letters
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Illinois Freedom of Information Act., I hereby request the following records:

Records sufficient to show copies of Parent Restriction letters issued from July, 2024 to current for the following schools/instances:

1. Any letters issued by schools in Network Fourteen, including issued by the Network Office:

These may also be listed as "Violation of Visitor Protocol" letters. Please note that I am not seeking any personally identifiable information or otherwise exempt information. As required by the statute, please ensure that the requested documents are redacted rather than exempting the entirety of the document. Additionally, for any and all exemptions used to redact exempt information, please provide clear and convincing evidence for each exemption used by your agency.

This request is made on behalf of The FOIA Bakery. Because this request is in the public interest for Illinois nonprofit The FOIA Bakery’s work to advocate for public education, please waive any fees in accordance with 5 ILCS § 140/6(c). Feel free to contact me with any questions, or if clarification is needed.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Miriam Bhimani

Please be advised that parent/guardian information was redacted pursuant to 5 ILCS 140/7.5 (r) which exempts from inspection or copying information prohibited from being disclosed by the Illinois School Student Records Act (ISSRA). ISSRA generally prohibits the disclosure of “school student records” and defines a “school student record” as “any writing or other recorded information concerning a student and by which a student may be individually identified, maintained by a school or at is direction or by an employee of a school, regardless of how or where the information is stored.” (105 ILCS 10/2(d). 
Section 7(1)(c) exempts personal information contained within public records, the disclosure of which would constitute a clearly unwarranted invasion of personal privacy, unless the disclosure is consented to in writing by the individual subject of the information. “Unwarranted invasion of personal privacy” means the disclosure of information that is highly personal or objectionable to a reasonable person and in which the subject’s right to privacy outweighs any legitimate public interest in obtaining the information. You have a right to have the denial of your request reviewed by the Public Access Counselor (PAC) at the Office of the Illinois Attorney General. 5 ILCS 140/9.5(a). You can file your Request for Review with the PAC by writing to: Leah Bartelt; Public Access Counselor Office of the Attorney General 500 South 2nd Street Springfield, Illinois 62706 E-mail: public.access@ilag.gov 877-299-3642 You also have the right to seek judicial review of your denial by filing a lawsuit in the State circuit court. 5 ILCS 140/11. If you choose to file a Request for Review with the PAC, you must do so within 60 calendar days of the date of this denial letter. 5 ILCS 140/9.5(a). Please note that you must include a copy of your original FOIA request and this denial letter when filing a Request for Review with the PAC.
